      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE STEEL DRAGON (1) came from this barrier and chased a handy one when third at this venue last week, his second placing in three outings since coming from the back line to score at Bendigo. This looks a winnable assignment. THE NAKED ART (8) found winning form two back at Horsham before a solid fourth here last week. Draws for a trail and could be dangerous. There was plenty to like about the last-start effort of PATIRO NZ (10) when fourth from this barrier in a stronger-line up. May need luck but this suits. OZZIE CORKA (9) might also need things to go his way given the second row draw but he was good when placed behind a handy one here last week. HIGHLANDHARTBREAKA (7) was held up last time but was racing well prior so is worth another chance.",
